cs.CR, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.NA, cs.DS 

The paper discusses a new family of cryptographically secure pseudorandom number generators, which falls under the category of cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also mentions the use of information theory (cs.IT) in the design of the generator. The use of coupled chaotic maps suggests a potential application in control systems (cs.SY) and numerical analysis (cs.NA). Finally, the modification of the maps and perturbation of their bits suggests a potential application in data structures (cs.DS).
